parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator assembly can cause the vehicle to speed up unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle speeds up unexpectedly when braking
dashboard lights come on
and the brake actuator assembly fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic liftgate can cause the liftgate to not open or close properly, leading to inconvenience and potential safety issues.
symptoms: The liftgate does not open or close properly
requiring manual intervention to open or close it.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter/solenoid can cause a fire, leading to damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
with the fire originating from the front of the vehicle on the driver's side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty rear hatch sensor can cause the door ajar warning light to come on, leading to distraction and potential safety issues.
symptoms: The door ajar warning light comes on
interior lights turn on
and a beeping sound occurs
even when the doors are closed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty door sensor can cause the door ajar warning light to come on, leading to distraction and potential safety issues.
symptoms: The door ajar warning light comes on
interior lights turn on
and a beeping sound occurs
even when the doors are closed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Actuator and Brake Booster Pump Assembly Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator and brake booster pump assembly can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential injury or death.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
ABS warning light
traction control light
and brake system warning light illuminate on the dashboard
loud noise from the brake booster pump
and vibrations when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the brake system and disablement of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake malfunction warning light
ABS warning light
traction control light
and brake system warning light illuminate on the dashboard
loss of brake power
and extended stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Fade and Delayed Response
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pedal fade and delayed response can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal takes longer to respond
and extended stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure and Loss of Brake Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system and loss of brake power can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Complete loss of brake power
brake pedal goes to the floor
and extended stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected shattering of the sun roof glass can cause driver distraction, loss of visibility, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The sun roof glass explodes or shatters without warning
causing glass fragments to fall into the passenger compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's side sun visor can cause driver distraction, loss of visibility, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The sun visor falls down or does not stay in the up position
obstructing the driver's view of the road.
